{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm an ecologist,"},{"time":3000,"text":"mostly a coral reef ecologist."},{"time":5000,"text":"I started out in Chesapeake Bay"},{"time":7000,"text":"and went diving in the winter"},{"time":9000,"text":"and became a tropical ecologist overnight."},{"time":12000,"text":"And it was really a lot of fun"},{"time":15000,"text":"for about 10 years."},{"time":17000,"text":"I mean, somebody pays you"},{"time":19000,"text":"to go around and travel"},{"time":21000,"text":"and look at some of the most"},{"time":23000,"text":"beautiful places on the planet."},{"time":25000,"text":"And that was what I did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"And I ended up in Jamaica,"},{"time":30000,"text":"in the West Indies,"},{"time":32000,"text":"where the coral reefs were really"},{"time":34000,"text":"among the most extraordinary, structurally,"},{"time":36000,"text":"that I ever saw in my life."},{"time":39000,"text":"And this picture here,"},{"time":41000,"text":"it's really interesting, it shows two things:"},{"time":43000,"text":"First of all, it's in black and white"},{"time":45000,"text":"because the water was so clear"},{"time":47000,"text":"and you could see so far,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and film was so slow"},{"time":51000,"text":"in the 1960s and early 70s,"},{"time":53000,"text":"you took pictures in black and white."},{"time":55000,"text":"The other thing it shows you"},{"time":57000,"text":"is that, although there's this beautiful"},{"time":59000,"text":"forest of coral,"},{"time":61000,"text":"there are no fish in that picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"Those reefs at Discovery Bay, Jamaica"},{"time":67000,"text":"were the most studied coral reefs"},{"time":69000,"text":"in the world for 20 years."},{"time":71000,"text":"We were the best and the brightest."},{"time":73000,"text":"People came to study our reefs from Australia,"},{"time":76000,"text":"which is sort of funny"},{"time":78000,"text":"because now we go to theirs."},{"time":80000,"text":"And the view of scientists"},{"time":83000,"text":"about how coral reefs work, how they ought to be,"},{"time":86000,"text":"was based on these reefs"},{"time":88000,"text":"without any fish."},{"time":90000,"text":"Then, in 1980,"},{"time":92000,"text":"there was a hurricane, Hurricane Allen."},{"time":95000,"text":"I put half the lab"},{"time":97000,"text":"up in my house."},{"time":99000,"text":"The wind blew very strong."},{"time":101000,"text":"The waves were 25"},{"time":104000,"text":"to 50 feet high."},{"time":106000,"text":"And the reefs disappeared, and new islands formed,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and we thought, \"Well, we're real smart."},{"time":111000,"text":"We know that hurricanes"},{"time":113000,"text":"have always happened in the past.\""},{"time":115000,"text":"And we published a paper in Science,"},{"time":117000,"text":"the first time that anybody ever"},{"time":119000,"text":"described the destruction"},{"time":121000,"text":"on a coral reef by a major hurricane."},{"time":124000,"text":"And we predicted what would happen,"},{"time":126000,"text":"and we got it all wrong."},{"time":128000,"text":"And the reason was"},{"time":130000,"text":"because of overfishing,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and the fact that a last common grazer,"},{"time":136000,"text":"a sea urchin, died."},{"time":139000,"text":"And within a few months"},{"time":141000,"text":"after that sea urchin dying, the seaweed started to grow."},{"time":144000,"text":"And that is the same reef;"},{"time":146000,"text":"that's the same reef 15 years ago;"},{"time":148000,"text":"that's the same reef today."},{"time":151000,"text":"The coral reefs of the north coast of Jamaica"},{"time":154000,"text":"have a few percent live coral cover"},{"time":157000,"text":"and a lot of seaweed and slime."},{"time":159000,"text":"And that's more or less the story"},{"time":161000,"text":"of the coral reefs of the Caribbean,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and increasingly, tragically,"},{"time":166000,"text":"the coral reefs worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"Now, that's my little, depressing story."},{"time":171000,"text":"All of us in our 60s and 70s"},{"time":174000,"text":"have comparable depressing stories."},{"time":177000,"text":"There are tens of thousands"},{"time":179000,"text":"of those stories out there,"},{"time":181000,"text":"and it's really hard to conjure up"},{"time":183000,"text":"much of a sense of well-being,"},{"time":185000,"text":"because it just keeps getting worse."},{"time":187000,"text":"And the reason it keeps getting worse"},{"time":189000,"text":"is that after a natural catastrophe,"},{"time":192000,"text":"like a hurricane,"},{"time":196000,"text":"it used to be that there was"},{"time":198000,"text":"some kind of successional sequence of recovery,"},{"time":201000,"text":"but what's going on now is that"},{"time":204000,"text":"overfishing and pollution and climate change"},{"time":207000,"text":"are all interacting"},{"time":209000,"text":"in a way that prevents that."},{"time":211000,"text":"And so I'm going to sort of go through"},{"time":213000,"text":"and talk about those three"},{"time":215000,"text":"kinds of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"We hear a lot about"},{"time":219000,"text":"the collapse of cod."},{"time":221000,"text":"It's difficult to imagine that"},{"time":223000,"text":"two, or some historians would say three world wars"},{"time":227000,"text":"were fought during the colonial era"},{"time":229000,"text":"for the control of cod."},{"time":231000,"text":"Cod fed most of the people of Western Europe."},{"time":234000,"text":"It fed the slaves"},{"time":236000,"text":"brought to the Antilles,"},{"time":239000,"text":"the song \"Jamaica Farewell\" --"},{"time":241000,"text":"\"Ackee rice salt fish are nice\" --"},{"time":243000,"text":"is an emblem of the importance"},{"time":246000,"text":"of salt cod from northeastern Canada."},{"time":249000,"text":"It all collapsed in the 80s and the 90s:"},{"time":252000,"text":"35,000 people lost their jobs."},{"time":255000,"text":"And that was the beginning"},{"time":257000,"text":"of a kind of serial depletion"},{"time":259000,"text":"from bigger and tastier species"},{"time":261000,"text":"to smaller and not-so-tasty species,"},{"time":264000,"text":"from species that were near to home"},{"time":266000,"text":"to species that were all around the world,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and what have you."},{"time":271000,"text":"It's a little hard to understand that,"},{"time":273000,"text":"because you can go to a Costco in the United States"},{"time":276000,"text":"and buy cheap fish."},{"time":278000,"text":"You ought to read the label to find out where it came from,"},{"time":280000,"text":"but it's still cheap,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and everybody thinks it's okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"It's hard to communicate this,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and one way that I think is really interesting"},{"time":289000,"text":"is to talk about sport fish,"},{"time":292000,"text":"because people like to go out and catch fish."},{"time":295000,"text":"It's one of those things."},{"time":297000,"text":"This picture here shows the trophy fish,"},{"time":300000,"text":"the biggest fish caught"},{"time":302000,"text":"by people who pay a lot of money"},{"time":304000,"text":"to get on a boat,"},{"time":306000,"text":"go to a place off of Key West in Florida,"},{"time":309000,"text":"drink a lot of beer,"},{"time":311000,"text":"throw a lot of hooks and lines into the water,"},{"time":313000,"text":"come back with the biggest and the best fish,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and the champion trophy fish"},{"time":318000,"text":"are put on this board, where people take a picture,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and this guy is obviously"},{"time":323000,"text":"really excited about that fish."},{"time":326000,"text":"Well, that's what it's like now,"},{"time":328000,"text":"but this is what it was like in the 1950s"},{"time":330000,"text":"from the same boat in the same place"},{"time":333000,"text":"on the same board on the same dock."},{"time":336000,"text":"The trophy fish"},{"time":338000,"text":"were so big"},{"time":340000,"text":"that you couldn't put any of those small fish up on it."},{"time":343000,"text":"And the average size trophy fish"},{"time":345000,"text":"weighed 250 to 300 pounds, goliath grouper,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and if you wanted to go out and kill something,"},{"time":350000,"text":"you could pretty much count on"},{"time":352000,"text":"being able to catch one of those fish."},{"time":354000,"text":"And they tasted really good."},{"time":356000,"text":"And people paid less in 1950 dollars"},{"time":359000,"text":"to catch that"},{"time":361000,"text":"than what people pay now"},{"time":363000,"text":"to catch those little, tiny fish."},{"time":366000,"text":"And that's everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"It's not just the fish, though,"},{"time":370000,"text":"that are disappearing."},{"time":372000,"text":"Industrial fishing uses big stuff,"},{"time":375000,"text":"big machinery."},{"time":377000,"text":"We use nets that are 20 miles long."},{"time":379000,"text":"We use longlines"},{"time":381000,"text":"that have one million or two million hooks."},{"time":384000,"text":"And we trawl,"},{"time":386000,"text":"which means to take something"},{"time":388000,"text":"the size of a tractor trailer truck"},{"time":390000,"text":"that weighs thousands and thousands of pounds,"},{"time":393000,"text":"put it on a big chain,"},{"time":395000,"text":"and drag it across the sea floor"},{"time":397000,"text":"to stir up the bottom and catch the fish."},{"time":400000,"text":"Think of it as"},{"time":403000,"text":"being kind of the bulldozing of a city"},{"time":405000,"text":"or of a forest,"},{"time":407000,"text":"because it clears it away."},{"time":409000,"text":"And the habitat destruction"},{"time":411000,"text":"is unbelievable."},{"time":413000,"text":"This is a photograph,"},{"time":415000,"text":"a typical photograph,"},{"time":417000,"text":"of what the continental shelves"},{"time":419000,"text":"of the world look like."},{"time":421000,"text":"You can see the rows in the bottom,"},{"time":424000,"text":"the way you can see the rows"},{"time":426000,"text":"in a field that has just been plowed"},{"time":428000,"text":"to plant corn."},{"time":430000,"text":"What that was, was a forest of sponges and coral,"},{"time":433000,"text":"which is a critical habitat"},{"time":435000,"text":"for the development of fish."},{"time":437000,"text":"What it is now is mud,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and the area of the ocean floor"},{"time":443000,"text":"that has been transformed from forest"},{"time":446000,"text":"to level mud, to parking lot,"},{"time":448000,"text":"is equivalent to the entire area"},{"time":451000,"text":"of all the forests"},{"time":453000,"text":"that have ever been cut down"},{"time":455000,"text":"on all of the earth"},{"time":457000,"text":"in the history of humanity."},{"time":459000,"text":"We've managed to do that"},{"time":461000,"text":"in the last 100 to 150 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"We tend to think of oil spills"},{"time":467000,"text":"and mercury"},{"time":469000,"text":"and we hear a lot about plastic these days."},{"time":471000,"text":"And all of that stuff is really disgusting,"},{"time":473000,"text":"but what's really insidious"},{"time":475000,"text":"is the biological pollution that happens"},{"time":478000,"text":"because of the magnitude of the shifts"},{"time":481000,"text":"that it causes"},{"time":483000,"text":"to entire ecosystems."},{"time":485000,"text":"And I'm going to just talk very briefly"},{"time":487000,"text":"about two kinds of biological pollution:"},{"time":490000,"text":"one is introduced species"},{"time":492000,"text":"and the other is what comes from nutrients."},{"time":495000,"text":"So this is the infamous"},{"time":497000,"text":"Caulerpa taxifolia,"},{"time":499000,"text":"the so-called killer algae."},{"time":502000,"text":"A book was written about it."},{"time":504000,"text":"It's a bit of an embarrassment."},{"time":506000,"text":"It was accidentally released"},{"time":508000,"text":"from the aquarium in Monaco,"},{"time":510000,"text":"it was bred to be cold tolerant"},{"time":513000,"text":"to have in peoples aquaria."},{"time":515000,"text":"It's very pretty,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and it has rapidly started"},{"time":519000,"text":"to overgrow"},{"time":521000,"text":"the once very rich"},{"time":523000,"text":"biodiversity of the"},{"time":525000,"text":"northwestern Mediterranean."},{"time":527000,"text":"I don't know how many of you remember the movie"},{"time":529000,"text":"\"The Little Shop of Horrors,\""},{"time":531000,"text":"but this is the plant of \"The Little Shop of Horrors.\""},{"time":534000,"text":"But, instead of devouring the people in the shop,"},{"time":537000,"text":"what it's doing is overgrowing"},{"time":539000,"text":"and smothering"},{"time":541000,"text":"virtually all of the bottom-dwelling life"},{"time":544000,"text":"of the entire northwestern"},{"time":547000,"text":"Mediterranean Sea."},{"time":549000,"text":"We don't know anything that eats it,"},{"time":551000,"text":"we're trying to do all sorts of genetics"},{"time":553000,"text":"and figure out something that could be done,"},{"time":556000,"text":"but, as it stands, it's the monster from hell,"},{"time":559000,"text":"about which nobody knows what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"Now another form of pollution"},{"time":565000,"text":"that's biological pollution"},{"time":567000,"text":"is what happens from excess nutrients."},{"time":569000,"text":"The green revolution,"},{"time":571000,"text":"all of this artificial nitrogen fertilizer, we use too much of it."},{"time":574000,"text":"It's subsidized, which is one of the reasons we used too much of it."},{"time":577000,"text":"It runs down the rivers,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and it feeds the plankton,"},{"time":581000,"text":"the little microscopic plant cells"},{"time":583000,"text":"in the coastal water."},{"time":585000,"text":"But since we ate all the oysters"},{"time":587000,"text":"and we ate all the fish that would eat the plankton,"},{"time":589000,"text":"there's nothing to eat the plankton"},{"time":591000,"text":"and there's more and more of it,"},{"time":593000,"text":"so it dies of old age,"},{"time":595000,"text":"which is unheard of for plankton."},{"time":597000,"text":"And when it dies, it falls to the bottom"},{"time":599000,"text":"and then it rots,"},{"time":601000,"text":"which means that bacteria break it down."},{"time":603000,"text":"And in the process"},{"time":605000,"text":"they use up all the oxygen,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and in using up all the oxygen"},{"time":609000,"text":"they make the environment utterly lethal"},{"time":611000,"text":"for anything that can't swim away."},{"time":613000,"text":"So, what we end up with"},{"time":615000,"text":"is a microbial zoo"},{"time":617000,"text":"dominated by bacteria"},{"time":619000,"text":"and jellyfish, as you see"},{"time":621000,"text":"on the left in front of you."},{"time":623000,"text":"And the only fishery left --"},{"time":625000,"text":"and it is a commercial fishery --"},{"time":627000,"text":"is the jellyfish fishery"},{"time":629000,"text":"you see on the right, where there used to be prawns."},{"time":631000,"text":"Even in Newfoundland"},{"time":633000,"text":"where we used to catch cod,"},{"time":635000,"text":"we now have a jellyfish fishery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"And another version of this sort of thing"},{"time":640000,"text":"is what is often called red tides"},{"time":642000,"text":"or toxic blooms."},{"time":644000,"text":"That picture on the left is just staggering to me."},{"time":647000,"text":"I have talked about it a million times,"},{"time":649000,"text":"but it's unbelievable."},{"time":651000,"text":"In the upper right of that picture on the left"},{"time":653000,"text":"is almost the Mississippi Delta,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and the lower left of that picture"},{"time":657000,"text":"is the Texas-Mexico border."},{"time":659000,"text":"You're looking at the entire"},{"time":661000,"text":"northwestern Gulf of Mexico;"},{"time":663000,"text":"you're looking at one toxic"},{"time":665000,"text":"dinoflagellate bloom that can kill fish,"},{"time":667000,"text":"made by that beautiful little creature"},{"time":669000,"text":"on the lower right."},{"time":671000,"text":"And in the upper right you see this"},{"time":673000,"text":"black sort of cloud"},{"time":675000,"text":"moving ashore."},{"time":677000,"text":"That's the same species."},{"time":679000,"text":"And as it comes to shore and the wind blows,"},{"time":682000,"text":"and little droplets of the water get into the air,"},{"time":685000,"text":"the emergency rooms of all the hospitals fill up"},{"time":688000,"text":"with people with acute respiratory distress."},{"time":690000,"text":"And that's retirement homes"},{"time":692000,"text":"on the west coast of Florida."},{"time":694000,"text":"A friend and I did this thing in Hollywood"},{"time":696000,"text":"we called Hollywood ocean night,"},{"time":698000,"text":"and I was trying to figure out how to"},{"time":700000,"text":"explain to actors what's going on."},{"time":702000,"text":"And I said,"},{"time":704000,"text":"\"So, imagine you're in a movie called 'Escape from Malibu'"},{"time":707000,"text":"because all the beautiful people have moved"},{"time":709000,"text":"to North Dakota, where it's clean and safe."},{"time":711000,"text":"And the only people who are left there"},{"time":713000,"text":"are the people who can't afford"},{"time":716000,"text":"to move away from the coast,"},{"time":718000,"text":"because the coast, instead of being paradise,"},{"time":721000,"text":"is harmful to your health.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":723000,"text":"And then this is amazing."},{"time":725000,"text":"It was when I was on holiday last early autumn in France."},{"time":728000,"text":"This is from the coast of Brittany,"},{"time":730000,"text":"which is being enveloped"},{"time":732000,"text":"in this green, algal slime."},{"time":735000,"text":"The reason that it attracted so much attention,"},{"time":738000,"text":"besides the fact that it's disgusting,"},{"time":741000,"text":"is that sea birds flying over it"},{"time":743000,"text":"are asphyxiated by the smell and die,"},{"time":746000,"text":"and a farmer died of it,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and you can imagine the scandal that happened."},{"time":750000,"text":"And so there's this war"},{"time":752000,"text":"between the farmers"},{"time":754000,"text":"and the fishermen about it all,"},{"time":756000,"text":"and the net result is that"},{"time":758000,"text":"the beaches of Brittany have to be bulldozed of this stuff"},{"time":761000,"text":"on a regular basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"And then, of course, there's climate change,"},{"time":765000,"text":"and we all know about climate change."},{"time":767000,"text":"I guess the iconic figure of it"},{"time":769000,"text":"is the melting of the ice"},{"time":771000,"text":"in the Arctic Sea."},{"time":773000,"text":"Think about the thousands and thousands of people who died"},{"time":776000,"text":"trying to find the Northwest Passage."},{"time":779000,"text":"Well, the Northwest Passage is already there."},{"time":781000,"text":"I think it's sort of funny;"},{"time":783000,"text":"it's on the Siberian coast,"},{"time":785000,"text":"maybe the Russians will charge tolls."},{"time":788000,"text":"The governments of the world"},{"time":790000,"text":"are taking this really seriously."},{"time":792000,"text":"The military of the Arctic nations"},{"time":795000,"text":"is taking it really seriously."},{"time":798000,"text":"For all the denial of climate change"},{"time":800000,"text":"by government leaders,"},{"time":802000,"text":"the CIA"},{"time":804000,"text":"and the navies of Norway"},{"time":806000,"text":"and the U.S. and Canada, whatever"},{"time":809000,"text":"are busily thinking about"},{"time":811000,"text":"how they will secure their territory"},{"time":814000,"text":"in this inevitability"},{"time":817000,"text":"from their point of view."},{"time":819000,"text":"And, of course, Arctic communities are toast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"The other kinds of effects of climate change --"},{"time":823000,"text":"this is coral bleaching. It's a beautiful picture, right?"},{"time":825000,"text":"All that white coral."},{"time":827000,"text":"Except it's supposed to be brown."},{"time":830000,"text":"What happens is that"},{"time":832000,"text":"the corals are a symbiosis,"},{"time":834000,"text":"and they have these little algal cells"},{"time":836000,"text":"that live inside them."},{"time":838000,"text":"And the algae give the corals sugar,"},{"time":840000,"text":"and the corals give the algae"},{"time":842000,"text":"nutrients and protection."},{"time":844000,"text":"But when it gets too hot,"},{"time":846000,"text":"the algae can't make the sugar."},{"time":848000,"text":"The corals say, \"You cheated. You didn't pay your rent.\""},{"time":850000,"text":"They kick them out, and then they die."},{"time":853000,"text":"Not all of them die; some of them survive,"},{"time":855000,"text":"some more are surviving,"},{"time":857000,"text":"but it's really bad news."},{"time":859000,"text":"To try and give you a sense of this,"},{"time":861000,"text":"imagine you go camping in July"},{"time":864000,"text":"somewhere in Europe or in North America,"},{"time":867000,"text":"and you wake up the next morning, and you look around you,"},{"time":869000,"text":"and you see that 80 percent of the trees,"},{"time":871000,"text":"as far as you can see,"},{"time":873000,"text":"have dropped their leaves and are standing there naked."},{"time":876000,"text":"And you come home, and you discover"},{"time":878000,"text":"that 80 percent of all the trees"},{"time":880000,"text":"in North America and in Europe"},{"time":882000,"text":"have dropped their leaves."},{"time":884000,"text":"And then you read in the paper a few weeks later,"},{"time":886000,"text":"\"Oh, by the way, a quarter of those died.\""},{"time":889000,"text":"Well, that's what happened in the Indian Ocean"},{"time":892000,"text":"during the 1998 El Nino,"},{"time":894000,"text":"an area vastly greater"},{"time":896000,"text":"than the size of North America and Europe,"},{"time":898000,"text":"when 80 percent of all the corals bleached"},{"time":901000,"text":"and a quarter of them died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"And then the really scary thing"},{"time":906000,"text":"about all of this --"},{"time":908000,"text":"the overfishing, the pollution and the climate change --"},{"time":911000,"text":"is that each thing doesn't happen in a vacuum."},{"time":914000,"text":"But there are these, what we call, positive feedbacks,"},{"time":917000,"text":"the synergies among them"},{"time":919000,"text":"that make the whole vastly greater"},{"time":921000,"text":"than the sum of the parts."},{"time":923000,"text":"And the great scientific challenge"},{"time":926000,"text":"for people like me in thinking about all this,"},{"time":929000,"text":"is do we know how"},{"time":931000,"text":"to put Humpty Dumpty back together again?"},{"time":934000,"text":"I mean, because we, at this point, we can protect it."},{"time":937000,"text":"But what does that mean?"},{"time":939000,"text":"We really don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"So what are the oceans going to be like"},{"time":945000,"text":"in 20 or 50 years?"},{"time":948000,"text":"Well, there won't be any fish"},{"time":950000,"text":"except for minnows,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and the water will be pretty dirty,"},{"time":955000,"text":"and all those kinds of things"},{"time":957000,"text":"and full of mercury, etc., etc."},{"time":962000,"text":"And dead zones will get bigger and bigger"},{"time":964000,"text":"and they'll start to merge,"},{"time":966000,"text":"and we can imagine something like"},{"time":968000,"text":"the dead-zonification"},{"time":970000,"text":"of the global, coastal ocean."},{"time":973000,"text":"Then you sure won't want to eat fish that were raised in it,"},{"time":976000,"text":"because it would be a kind of"},{"time":978000,"text":"gastronomic Russian roulette."},{"time":980000,"text":"Sometimes you have a toxic bloom;"},{"time":982000,"text":"sometimes you don't."},{"time":984000,"text":"That doesn't sell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"The really scary things though"},{"time":988000,"text":"are the physical, chemical,"},{"time":991000,"text":"oceanographic things that are happening."},{"time":994000,"text":"As the surface of the ocean gets warmer,"},{"time":997000,"text":"the water is lighter when it's warmer,"},{"time":999000,"text":"it becomes harder and harder"},{"time":1001000,"text":"to turn the ocean over."},{"time":1003000,"text":"We say it becomes"},{"time":1005000,"text":"more strongly stratified."},{"time":1007000,"text":"The consequence of that is that"},{"time":1009000,"text":"all those nutrients"},{"time":1011000,"text":"that fuel the great anchoveta fisheries,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"of the sardines of California"},{"time":1016000,"text":"or in Peru or whatever,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"those slow down"},{"time":1021000,"text":"and those fisheries collapse."},{"time":1023000,"text":"And, at the same time,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"water from the surface, which is rich in oxygen,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"doesn't make it down"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and the ocean turns into a desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035000,"text":"So the question is: How are we all"},{"time":1037000,"text":"going to respond to this?"},{"time":1039000,"text":"And we can do"},{"time":1041000,"text":"all sorts of things to fix it,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"but in the final analysis,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"the thing we really need to fix"},{"time":1047000,"text":"is ourselves."},{"time":1049000,"text":"It's not about the fish; it's not about the pollution;"},{"time":1052000,"text":"it's not about the climate change."},{"time":1054000,"text":"It's about us"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and our greed and our need for growth"},{"time":1059000,"text":"and our inability to imagine a world"},{"time":1062000,"text":"that is different from the selfish world"},{"time":1064000,"text":"we live in today."},{"time":1066000,"text":"So the question is: Will we respond to this or not?"},{"time":1069000,"text":"I would say that the future of life"},{"time":1071000,"text":"and the dignity of human beings"},{"time":1073000,"text":"depends on our doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}